===Etymology 1===
From {{F.}} ''[[#French|absent]]'' < {{L.}} ''[[absent-]]'', the stem of ''[[absens]]'', present participle of ''[[abesse]]'', ‘to be away from’, formed from ''[[ab]]'' + ''[[esse]]'' ‘to be’.

====Pronunciation====
* {{italbrac|[[RP]] & US}} {{enPR|ăb'sənt}}, {{IPA|/ˈæbsənt/}}, {{SAMPA|/{bs@nt/}}

====Adjective====
{{en-adj|-}}

# Being [[away]] from a place; [[withdrawn]] from a place; not [[present]].
#: {{rfdate}} ''Expecting '''absent''' friends.'' — {{Shak.}}, ''All’s Well That Ends Well, II-iii''
# Not [[exist]]ing; [[lack]]ing.
#: ''The part was rudimental or '''absent'''.''
# [[inattentive|Inattentive]] to what is passing; [[absent-minded]]; [[preoccupied]].
#: {{rfdate}} ''What is commonly called an '''absent''' man is commonly either a very weak or a very affected man.'' — Chesterfield

